Reasoning: The paper proposes a novel adversarial distillation mechanism for model compression and knowledge transfer without any real-world data. This involves the use of a generator to produce "hard samples" to reduce the discrepancy between the student and teacher models. This work is relevant to several sub-categories of computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), natural language processing (cs.CL), and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE).
